Appendix E: Installation and Setup Guide
The following step-by-step guide describes how to install and run the application on a fresh Windows 11 machine.

E.1 Prerequisites
•	Python 3.10 or later installed — download from https://www.python.org/downloads/
•	MySQL 8.0 Community Server installed — download from https://dev.mysql.com/downloads/mysql/
•	Git installed — download from https://git-scm.com/download/win
•	A terminal application (Windows Command Prompt, PowerShell, or Windows Terminal)

E.2 Installation Steps
Step 1 — Clone the Repository
git clone https://github.com/Saeesh4/inventory-management-system.git
cd inventory-management-system

Step 2 — Install Python Dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

Step 3 — Set Up the MySQL Database
mysql -u root -p
source schema.sql
exit

Step 4 — Create the .env File
Create a file named .env in the project root folder with the following content (replace values as appropriate):
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_USER=root
DB_PASSWORD=your_mysql_password
DB_NAME=inventory_db
SECRET_KEY=your_random_secret_key_here

Step 5 — Generate Historical Data (Optional)
py generate_data.py

Step 6 — Run the Application
py app.py

Step 7 — Open in Browser
Navigate to http://127.0.0.1:5000 in your browser. Log in with:
Username: admin
Password: admin123

